{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/diarrhoea-adults-assessment/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"64c13816-2ca8-5502-aadf-244f01fbe16a","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 9128c32f-397d-46e5-a4c6-a7f20188fe26 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 9128c32f-397d-46e5-a4c6-a7f20188fe26 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item a3624fc5-afad-4c43-918a-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field b818ca62-a3d0-4361-9060-a7f20188fe26 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field b818ca62-a3d0-4361-9060-a7f20188fe26 --><!-- begin field e498e4fc-b0c7-4625-b6e3-a7f20188fe26 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field e498e4fc-b0c7-4625-b6e3-a7f20188fe26 --><!-- begin field ae50e30f-8f4f-4a80-a6b9-a7f20188fe26 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field ae50e30f-8f4f-4a80-a6b9-a7f20188fe26 --><!-- begin field 73cf5855-ee5d-4c0a-8561-a7f20188fe26 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 73cf5855-ee5d-4c0a-8561-a7f20188fe26 --><!-- begin field 268ac40b-01c1-478b-92c3-a7f20188fe26 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field 268ac40b-01c1-478b-92c3-a7f20188fe26 --><!-- begin field 5a6619d5-a944-433c-bc0f-a7f20188fe26 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 5a6619d5-a944-433c-bc0f-a7f20188fe26 --><!-- end item a3624fc5-afad-4c43-918a-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"6533613a-a6a0-5161-9e6d-cd4ee7e16f85","topicId":"828aa958-94ce-4c08-b7a9-8aae08eb04a1","topicName":"Diarrhoea - adult's assessment","slug":"diarrhoea-adults-assessment","lastRevised":"Last revised in December 2018","chapters":[{"id":"506b2cc6-f0d5-58b3-a742-aed362fa45d5","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9d304716-61b9-596f-b769-d04740407c6e","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"43e53ae4-7fa5-5ace-adb6-471fd5d9ba8b","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"1bd58366-044e-5365-b064-85d9b8f2bd14","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"8791d0e2-fe70-5573-a704-a1dfb542dab0","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"ed95659f-30b3-5441-bb51-cca45f53a32c","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"b9b92fe1-fc7d-5362-8311-314794c89d2e","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"2d13f20d-3413-5949-a1a2-aaf3badf7af8","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"74365bdf-fcf0-5355-bb87-aa2af08c64cb","slug":